name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: A unique identifier assigned to this immunization record.

name: $addidentifier
desc: A unique identifier assigned to this immunization record.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A unique identifier assigned to this immunization record.

name: $status
desc: Returns: Indicates the current status of the immunization event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indicates the current status of the immunization event.

name: $statusReason
desc: Returns: Indicates the reason the immunization event was not performed.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indicates the reason the immunization event was not performed.

name: $vaccineCode
desc: Returns: Vaccine that was administered or was to be administered.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Vaccine that was administered or was to be administered.

name: $patient
desc: Returns: The patient who either received or did not receive the immunization.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The patient who either received or did not receive the immunization.

name: $encounter
desc: Returns: The visit or admission or other contact between patient and health care provider the immunization was performed as part of.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The visit or admission or other contact between patient and health care provider the immunization was performed as part of.

name: $recorded
desc: Returns: The date the occurrence of the immunization was first captured in the record - potentially significantly after the occurrence of the event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date the occurrence of the immunization was first captured in the record - potentially significantly after the occurrence of the event.

name: $primarySource
desc: Returns: An indication that the content of the record is based on information from the person who administered the vaccine. This reflects the context under which the data was originally recorded.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: An indication that the content of the record is based on information from the person who administered the vaccine. This reflects the context under which the data was originally recorded.

name: $reportOrigin
desc: Returns: The source of the data when the report of the immunization event is not based on information from the person who administered the vaccine.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The source of the data when the report of the immunization event is not based on information from the person who administered the vaccine.

name: $location
desc: Returns: The service delivery location where the vaccine administration occurred.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The service delivery location where the vaccine administration occurred.

name: $manufacturer
desc: Returns: Name of vaccine manufacturer.

name: $lotNumber
desc: Returns: Lot number of the  vaccine product.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Lot number of the  vaccine product.

name: $expirationDate
desc: Returns: Date vaccine batch expires.

name: $site
desc: Returns: Body site where vaccine was administered.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Body site where vaccine was administered.

name: $route
desc: Returns: The path by which the vaccine product is taken into the body.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The path by which the vaccine product is taken into the body.

name: $doseQuantity
desc: Returns: The quantity of vaccine product that was administered.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The quantity of vaccine product that was administered.

name: $performer
desc: Returns: Indicates who performed the immunization event.

name: $addperformer
desc: Indicates who performed the immunization event.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Indicates who performed the immunization event.

name: $note
desc: Returns: Extra information about the immunization that is not conveyed by the other attributes.

name: $addnote
desc: Extra information about the immunization that is not conveyed by the other attributes.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Extra information about the immunization that is not conveyed by the other attributes.

name: $reasonCode
desc: Returns: Reasons why the vaccine was administered.

name: $addreasonCode
desc: Reasons why the vaccine was administered.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Reasons why the vaccine was administered.

name: $reasonReference
desc: Returns: Condition, Observation or DiagnosticReport that supports why the immunization was administered.

name: $addreasonReference
desc: Condition, Observation or DiagnosticReport that supports why the immunization was administered.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Condition, Observation or DiagnosticReport that supports why the immunization was administered.

name: $isSubpotent
desc: Returns: Indication if a dose is considered to be subpotent. By default, a dose should be considered to be potent.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indication if a dose is considered to be subpotent. By default, a dose should be considered to be potent.

name: $subpotentReason
desc: Returns: Reason why a dose is considered to be subpotent.

name: $addsubpotentReason
desc: Reason why a dose is considered to be subpotent.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Reason why a dose is considered to be subpotent.

name: $education
desc: Returns: Educational material presented to the patient (or guardian) at the time of vaccine administration.

name: $addeducation
desc: Educational material presented to the patient (or guardian) at the time of vaccine administration.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Educational material presented to the patient (or guardian) at the time of vaccine administration.

name: $programEligibility
desc: Returns: Indicates a patient's eligibility for a funding program.

name: $addprogramEligibility
desc: Indicates a patient's eligibility for a funding program.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Indicates a patient's eligibility for a funding program.

name: $fundingSource
desc: Returns: Indicates the source of the vaccine actually administered. This may be different than the patient eligibility (e.g. the patient may be eligible for a publically purchased vaccine but due to inventory issues, vaccine purchased with private funds was actually administered).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indicates the source of the vaccine actually administered. This may be different than the patient eligibility (e.g. the patient may be eligible for a publically purchased vaccine but due to inventory issues, vaccine purchased with private funds was actual

name: $reaction
desc: Returns: Categorical data indicating that an adverse event is associated in time to an immunization.

name: $addreaction
desc: Categorical data indicating that an adverse event is associated in time to an immunization.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Categorical data indicating that an adverse event is associated in time to an immunization.

name: $protocolApplied
desc: Returns: The protocol (set of recommendations) being followed by the provider who administered the dose.

name: $addprotocolApplied
desc: The protocol (set of recommendations) being followed by the provider who administered the dose.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The protocol (set of recommendations) being followed by the provider who administered the dose.
